.TH "devm_mbox_controller_register" 9 "devm_mbox_controller_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_mbox_controller_register \- managed mbox_controller_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_mbox_controller_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct mbox_controller *mbox "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device owning the mailbox controller being registered
.IP "mbox" 12
mailbox controller being registered
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function adds a device-managed resource that will make sure that the
mailbox controller, which is registered using \fBmbox_controller_register\fP
as part of this function, will be unregistered along with the rest of
device-managed resources upon driver probe failure or driver removal.

Returns 0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
